---
description: General Broadcast Graphics project rules
alwaysApply: true
---

Broadcast Graphics is an MVP for broadcast graphics. Preserve working demo
behavior over theoretical production hardening.

Read before significant work:

- `AGENTS.md`
- `SPEC.md`
- `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`
- `docs/CURSOR_WORKFLOW.md`
- `docs/CONTRACTS.md` when API/WS/schema changes are involved
- `docs/baseline-checklist.md` when behavior can be affected

Core rules:

- Respond to the user in Russian.
- Write human-facing project documentation in Russian.
- Keep `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` concise and directive.
- Read relevant files before editing.
- Keep changes scoped to the requested owner zone.
- If a task needs edits outside the owner zone, stop and ask before proceeding.
- Do not silently change shared schemas, API shapes, or WebSocket protocol.
- Do not mix feature work and broad refactoring unless explicitly requested.
- Do not add auth, complex DB, deployment platform, or broad dependency upgrades
  unless Karen explicitly asks.
- Do not edit plan files unless explicitly requested.
- Do not commit or push unless explicitly requested.
- Preserve the baseline in `docs/baseline-checklist.md`.

Current owner zones:

- Karen: architecture, backend core, shared contracts, LLM, repo process, docs, CI.
- Sergey: template editor, editor UI, canvas interactions, layer properties, variables, timeline UI.
- Vasily: templates, rundowns, control workflows, channels, external integrations.

Branch rules:

- `MVP` is the protected integration branch.
- `refactoring-v1` is Karen's foundation/team lead branch.
- Feature branches should be short-lived and owner-prefixed.
- All changes go through PR review by Karen before merging to `MVP`.

Before PR:

- `npm run typecheck`
- `npm run build`
- manual startup via `./start.sh`
- relevant manual scenario from `docs/baseline-checklist.md`
